article.headline: Auburn 82, Alabama A&amp,M 40
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- Tay Waller scored 14 points in 22 minutes to lead Auburn to an 82-40 rout over Alabama A&M on Monday night. Korvotney Barber finished with 11 points and eight rebounds for the Tigers (8-4). Frankie Sullivan added 12 points and six rebounds off the bench. Auburn senior Quantez Robertson chipped in with eight points, six rebounds and six assists. He became the fifth all-time assist leader in school history with 467 for his career. Auburn jumped out to an 18-6 lead early in the first half and never looked back. Waller had 12 first half points -- all on 3-pointers -- and the Tigers took a 46-28 halftime lead. Auburn was 0-for-4 from 3-point range in the second half, but the Bulldogs shot just 3-for-23 from the field in the final 20 minutes. The Bulldogs (2-6) were led by Trant Simpson, who scored 15 points.
